Impunity, arrogance or obeying orders. Those are the questions emerging following a phone conversation between Nairobi governor Mike Sonko and his Kiambu counterpart Ferdinand Waititu. In a leaked telephone conversation following the arrest of Waititu wife Susan Wangare over illegal construction of buildings, Sonko is heard saying he would release her illegally, and even gives orders on the amount of bail to be granted as he admits to be working on orders from above.